            "prompt": "Design the implementation plan for \"Return EBADF for untracked FDs instead of CONTINUE\" in the kbox seccomp supervisor.\n\n## Problem\nWhen a guest FD is not in the virtual FD table, I/O handlers (read, write, ioctl, etc.) return SECCOMP_USER_NOTIF_FLAG_CONTINUE, letting the host kernel handle the syscall. This is the second half of a TOCTOU escape: if the guest obtains a leaked host FD (via the openat TOCTOU race from TODO.md), it can read/write/ioctl on that FD freely.\n\n## Current Architecture\n- FD table has two ranges: low_fds[0..1024) and entries[32768..36864+)\n- `kbox_fd_table_get_lkl(fd)` returns: lkl_fd >= 0 for LKL-backed FDs, KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY (-2) for host-passthrough FDs (currently only shadow sockets), or -1 for completely untracked FDs\n- All I/O handlers check `if (lkl_fd < 0) return kbox_dispatch_continue()` — this is the vulnerability\n- Pipe FDs from forward_pipe2 are created via ADDFD but NOT tracked in the FD table\n- eventfd/eventfd2, timerfd_create, epoll_create1 are in DISPATCH_CONTINUE_TABLE — their created FDs are never tracked\n- stdio (0, 1, 2) are pre-existing host FDs, never tracked\n\n## Proposed Fix\nThe key insight: `kbox_fd_table_get_lkl()` already distinguishes -1 (no entry) from KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY (-2, host-passthrough entry exists). Change the pattern from:\n```c\nif (lkl_fd < 0) return kbox_dispatch_continue();\n```\nto:\n```c\nif (lkl_fd == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY) return kbox_dispatch_continue();\nif (lkl_fd < 0) return kbox_dispatch_errno(EBADF);\n```\n\nBut first, ensure all legitimate host-passthrough FDs are tracked:\n\n### Part 1: Track host-passthrough FDs\n\n1. **Pre-register stdio (0,1,2)** in seccomp-supervisor.c after kbox_fd_table_init():\n   ```c\n   for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)\n       kbox_fd_table_insert_at(&fd_table, i, KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY, i < 2 ? 0 : 0);\n   ```\n\n2. **Track pipe FDs** in dispatch-misc.c forward_pipe2() and the legacy pipe handler in seccomp-dispatch.c:\n   After ADDFD injection, call kbox_fd_table_insert_at(fd, KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY, 0) for each tracee FD.\n\n3. **Intercept eventfd/eventfd2**: Remove from DISPATCH_CONTINUE_TABLE and should_continue_fast(). Add forward_eventfd() handler that: calls eventfd() in supervisor, injects via ADDFD, tracks with KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY, closes supervisor copy.\n\n4. **Intercept timerfd_create**: Same pattern. calls timerfd_create() in supervisor, injects via ADDFD, tracks.\n\n5. **Intercept epoll_create1**: Same pattern. Though epoll FDs are only used with epoll_ctl/epoll_wait (which CONTINUE), tracking them closes a gap.\n\n### Part 2: Fix I/O handlers\n\nChange the CONTINUE-on-untracked-FD pattern in ALL these handlers:\n\nIn seccomp-dispatch.c:\n- forward_read_like (line 1765)\n- forward_write (line 1859)\n- forward_lseek (line 2069)\n- forward_fstat (line 2541)\n- forward_getdents_common (line 1466)\n- forward_sendfile (line 1970 — both-untracked case)\n\nIn dispatch-misc.c:\n- forward_pwrite64 (line 416)\n- dispatch_iov_transfer (line 501)\n- forward_ftruncate (line 613)\n- forward_fallocate (line 634)\n- forward_flock (line 658)\n- forward_fsync (line 673)\n- forward_fdatasync (line 693)\n- forward_ioctl (line 855)\n\nIn dispatch-exec.c:\n- forward_mmap (line 130 — untracked FD fallthrough)\n\n### Part 3: Handle dup/dup2/dup3/fcntl for host-passthrough FDs\n\n**forward_dup**: When lkl_fd == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY, CONTINUE the dup. But we can't track the result (don't see CONTINUE return value). Option: return EBADF (dup on a pipe is uncommon; shells use dup2). Alternative: emulate via /proc/pid/fd/N.\n\n**forward_dup2**: When lkl_old == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY: clean up stale newfd entry, insert host-passthrough at newfd, CONTINUE. This handles shell's `dup2(pipe_fd, stdout)`.\n\n**forward_dup3**: Same as dup2.\n\n**forward_fcntl**: When lkl_fd == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY: CONTINUE (host handles F_GETFL, F_SETFL etc. on pipe/eventfd). When lkl_fd == -1 AND find_by_host_fd fails: EBADF instead of CONTINUE.\n\n**forward_close**: Keep final CONTINUE at line 1753 — closing an untracked FD is harmless and cleans up leaks. But ADD a case for KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY with shadow_sp < 0: remove entry, then CONTINUE.\n\n### Part 4: Update DISPATCH tables\n\nRemove from DISPATCH_CONTINUE_TABLE: eventfd, eventfd2, timerfd_create, epoll_create1\nAdd to DISPATCH_HANDLER_TABLE: eventfd, eventfd2, timerfd_create, epoll_create1\n\nRemove from should_continue_fast(): same syscalls.\n\n## Edge Cases / Risks\n\n1. **FD gap [1024, 32768)**: If ADDFD allocates a pipe/eventfd FD in this range, insert_at fails. Log warning. This is pre-existing limitation.\n\n2. **fork() semantics**: After fork, child inherits host FDs. The FD table is supervisor-side, not per-process. Pipes shared between parent and child work because both hold the same host FD.\n\n3. **cloexec cleanup**: kbox_fd_table_close_cloexec checks lkl_fd != -1. KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY (-2) passes this check, so cloexec on host-passthrough FDs works correctly.\n\n4. **Busybox sendfile**: \"never return ENOSYS/EBADF for sendfile\" per MEMORY.md. For sendfile with both FDs untracked: now returns EBADF. But if both are host-passthrough, they should CONTINUE. Need to check for KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY in the both-untracked path.\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n1. src/dispatch-internal.h — Add forward declarations for new handlers\n2. src/dispatch-misc.c — Track pipes, new eventfd/timerfd/epoll handlers, fix I/O handlers\n3. src/seccomp-dispatch.c — Update tables, fix I/O handlers, fix dup/dup2/dup3/fcntl\n4. src/dispatch-exec.c — Fix mmap\n5. src/seccomp-supervisor.c — Pre-register stdio\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `make check-unit` — all 82 unit tests pass\n2. Integration: `./scripts/run-tests.sh ./kbox alpine.ext4` — 43 tests pass (pipe-based shell commands, busybox sendfile, etc.)\n3. Verify: eventfd/timerfd used by Alpine init or test programs still work\n4. Verify: shell pipe redirections (`echo f