            "plan": "# Plan: Return EBADF for untracked FDs instead of CONTINUE\n\n## Context\n\nSecurity fix for the second half of the CONTINUE escape (TODO.md P1). Once a guest obtains a leaked host FD via the openat TOCTOU race, it can freely read/write/ioctl that FD because the supervisor blindly CONTINUEs for any FD not in the virtual FD table. Fix: return EBADF for untracked FDs, CONTINUE only for explicitly tracked host-passthrough FDs.\n\n## Design\n\nKey insight: `kbox_fd_table_get_lkl()` returns -1 for untracked FDs and `KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY` (-2) for tracked host-passthrough entries. Change the universal pattern:\n\n```c\n// OLD: if (lkl_fd < 0) return kbox_dispatch_continue();\n// NEW:\nif (lkl_fd == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY)\n    return kbox_dispatch_continue();\nif (lkl_fd < 0)\n    return kbox_dispatch_errno(EBADF);\n```\n\nTwo logical commits for bisectability.\n\n---\n\n## Commit 1: Track all host-passthrough FDs\n\nAll behavior unchanged (lkl_fd < 0 still CONTINUEs for everything). This is pure preparation.\n\n### 1a. Pre-register stdio (0, 1, 2)\n\n**src/seccomp-supervisor.c** after line 604 (`kbox_fd_table_init`):\n```c\nfor (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)\n    kbox_fd_table_insert_at(&fd_table, i, KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY, 0);\n```\n\n**src/image.c** after line 580 (`kbox_fd_table_init`): same pattern.\n\n### 1b. Track pipe FDs\n\n**src/dispatch-misc.c `forward_pipe2()`** — after ADDFD and before guest_mem_write:\n```c\nkbox_fd_table_insert_at(ctx->fd_table, tracee_fd0, KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY, 0);\nkbox_fd_table_insert_at(ctx->fd_table, tracee_fd1, KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY, 0);\n```\n\n**src/seccomp-dispatch.c legacy pipe handler** (~line 3590): same pattern for tfd0, tfd1.\n\n### 1c. Intercept eventfd/eventfd2, timerfd_create, epoll_create1\n\nRemove from `DISPATCH_CONTINUE_TABLE` and `should_continue_fast()`.\n\nAdd handlers in **src/dispatch-misc.c** (pattern for each):\n1. Call syscall in supervisor (e.g., `eventfd(initval, flags)`)\n2. Inject via `request_addfd(ctx, req, host_fd, cloexec_flag)`\n3. Close supervisor copy\n4. `kbox_fd_table_insert_at(ctx->fd_table, tracee_fd, KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY, 0)`\n5. Set cloexec if requested\n6. Return tracee_fd\n\nAdd forward declarations in **src/dispatch-internal.h**.\nAdd entries in `DISPATCH_HANDLER_TABLE` in **src/seccomp-dispatch.c**.\n\n### 1d. Fix close_cloexec_entry for SHADOW_ONLY\n\n**src/fd-table.c `close_cloexec_entry()`** line 277: skip `kbox_lkl_close` for sentinel lkl_fd values:\n```c\nif (e->lkl_fd != -1 && e->cloexec) {\n    if (e->lkl_fd >= 0) {  // <-- add guard: only close real LKL FDs\n        if (!lkl_fd_has_other_ref(t, e, e->lkl_fd))\n            kbox_lkl_close(s, e->lkl_fd);\n    }\n    // rest unchanged\n```\n\n### 1e. Fix forward_close for host-passthrough without shadow_sp\n\n**src/seccomp-dispatch.c `forward_close()`** — broaden the SHADOW_ONLY check at line 1683 by removing the `shadow_sp >= 0` condition:\n```c\nif (entry && entry->lkl_fd == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY) {\n    kbox_fd_table_remove(ctx->fd_table, fd);\n    return kbox_dispatch_continue();\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Commit 2: Return EBADF for untracked FDs\n\n### 2a. I/O handlers — mechanical pattern change\n\nApply the two-step check in ALL these functions:\n\n**src/seccomp-dispatch.c:**\n- `forward_read_like` (line 1765)\n- `forward_write` (line 1859)\n- `forward_lseek` (line 2069)\n- `forward_fstat` (line 2541)\n- `forward_getdents_common` (line 1466)\n\n**src/dispatch-misc.c:**\n- `forward_pwrite64` (line 416)\n- `dispatch_iov_transfer` (line 501)\n- `forward_ftruncate` (line 613)\n- `forward_fallocate` (line 634)\n- `forward_flock` (line 658)\n- `forward_fsync` (line 673)\n- `forward_fdatasync` (line 693)\n\n**src/dispatch-exec.c:**\n- `forward_mmap` (line 130): change final `return kbox_dispatch_continue()` to check for SHADOW_ONLY before falling through to EBADF.\n\n### 2b. forward_ioctl — preserve TIOCSPGRP handling\n\n```c\nif (lkl_fd == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY) {\n    if (cmd == TIOCSPGRP || cmd == TIOCGPGRP || cmd == TIOCSCTTY)\n        return kbox_dispatch_errno(ENOTTY);\n    return kbox_dispatch_continue();\n}\nif (lkl_fd < 0)\n    return kbox_dispatch_errno(EBADF);\n```\n\n### 2c. forward_sendfile — handle host-passthrough pairs\n\n```c\nif (in_lkl < 0 && out_lkl < 0) {\n    if (in_lkl == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY &&\n        out_lkl == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY)\n        return kbox_dispatch_continue();\n    return kbox_dispatch_errno(EBADF);\n}\nif (in_lkl == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY)\n    return kbox_dispatch_errno(EBADF);  // can't emulate: no LKL FD\nif (in_lkl < 0)\n    return kbox_dispatch_errno(EBADF);\n```\n\n### 2d. forward_dup — EBADF for untracked, CONTINUE for host-passthrough\n\n```c\nif (lkl_fd == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY)\n    return kbox_dispatch_continue();  // host kernel dups it; result is untracked\nif (lkl_fd < 0) {\n    long orig_vfd = kbox_fd_table_find_by_host_fd(ctx->fd_table, fd);\n    if (orig_vfd < 0)\n        return kbox_dispatch_errno(EBADF);\n    // ... existing shadow socket dup handling unchanged ...\n```\n\n### 2e. forward_dup2/dup3 — track host-passthrough at newfd\n\nWhen oldfd is host-passthrough (lkl_old == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY):\n1. Handle oldfd == newfd → return newfd\n2. Clean up stale entry at newfd (existing logic)\n3. Insert KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY at newfd\n4. CONTINUE (host kernel does the dup2)\n\nWhen oldfd is untracked (lkl_old == -1 AND find_by_host_fd fails):\nReturn EBADF instead of CONTINUE.\n\n### 2f. forward_fcntl — EBADF for untracked, CONTINUE for host-passthrough\n\nAdd before the existing `if (lkl_fd < 0)` block:\n```c\nif (lkl_fd == KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY)\n    return kbox_dispatch_continue();\n```\nChange the final `return kbox_dispatch_continue()` inside the lkl_fd < 0 block to `return kbox_dispatch_errno(EBADF)`.\n\n---\n\n## Files Modified\n\n| File | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| src/seccomp-supervisor.c | Pre-register stdio |\n| src/image.c | Pre-register stdio 