            "content": "# Changelog\n\n## 2026-04-02: CONTINUE escape closure (issue #40)\n\nCommits: `0000ea9`, `0000182` (branch `ebadf`)\n\n### Deny I/O on untracked FDs / track host-passthrough (0000ea9)\n\n- Return EBADF for every untracked FD (lkl_fd == -1) in all I/O\n  handlers instead of CONTINUE.  Closes the second half of the CONTINUE\n  escape where a guest could read/write host FDs obtained via the openat\n  TOCTOU race.\n- Track all legitimate host-passthrough FDs as KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY:\n  stdio 0/1/2, pipe FDs, eventfd/timerfd/epoll (intercepted and injected\n  via ADDFD), /proc /sys /dev /TTY opens (emulated in supervisor),\n  dup/dup2/dup3/fcntl(F_DUPFD) results (via pidfd_getfd), inherited FDs\n  (one-time /proc/{pid}/fd scan).\n- Eliminate FD table gap [1024, 32768) with mid_fds[31744] array.\n  Convert all inline low_fds[]/entries[] lookups to fd_table_entry().\n- Move epoll_ctl/wait, timerfd_settime/gettime, fstatfs from CONTINUE\n  table to gated handlers with fd_should_deny_io validation.\n- Clear stale SHADOW_ONLY entries when ADDFD socket injection reuses a\n  tracked FD number (fixes bind EINVAL regression).\n- Preserve SHADOW_ONLY entries on close (shared table after fork);\n  skip them in close_cloexec_entry (host kernel handles exec).\n- Allow execve on /dev/fd/N, /dev/stdin, /dev/stdout, /dev/stderr.\n\n### Emulate path-dependent syscalls (0000182)\n\n- Replace every path-dependent CONTINUE with supervisor-side emulation\n  using local path copies and pidfd_getfd dirfd copies.  Closes the\n  TOCTOU window where a sibling thread mutates a path pointer between\n  process_vm_readv and the host kernel's re-read.\n- Emulated: fstatat, statx, stat, faccessat, readlinkat, symlinkat,\n  linkat, utimensat, mkdirat, unlinkat, fchmodat, fchownat, renameat2,\n  and legacy wrappers (access, mkdir, unlink, rmdir, chmod, chown).\n- Extract translate_proc_self() helper for /proc/self and\n  /proc/thread-self translation.\n- forward_execve: EACCES 