            "content": "# TODO\n\n## P1: Security\n\n- [x] **Eliminate CONTINUE for pointer-dependent syscalls** ([#40](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/40))\n  DONE (0000ea9, 0000182). All path-dependent CONTINUEs replaced with\n  supervisor-side emulation using local path copies and pidfd_getfd\n  dirfd copies.  openat/openat2/open emulated via ADDFD injection.\n  stat/statx/access/readlink/unlink/link/rename/symlink/mkdir/chmod/\n  chown/utimensat emulated via host syscalls in supervisor namespace.\n  execve returns EACCES for virtual paths. clone3 writes validated\n  flags back to guest memory before CONTINUE (residual TOCTOU is zero\n  risk for single-threaded guests).\n\n- [x] **Return EBADF for untracked FDs instead of CONTINUE**\n  DONE (0000ea9). All I/O handlers return EBADF for untracked FDs.\n  Pipes, eventfd, timerfd, epoll, stdio, and proc/dev/sys opens are\n  tracked as KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY. FD table gap [1024, 32768)\n  eliminated with mid_fds[] array. FD-consuming CONTINUE syscalls\n  (epoll_ctl, fstatfs, etc.) moved to handler table with deny checks.\n\n- [ ] **Add process_vm_readv to BPF deny list**\n  `process_vm_readv` (NR 310 x86_64, 270 aarch64) is not denied in the\n  BPF filter. Guest can read supervisor memory (same UID, child of\n  supervisor). Supervisor uses `process_vm_readv` on the child, not the\n  other way around; child has no legitimate reason to call it.\n\n- [ ] **Add clone3 namespace-flag regression tests**\n  No test covers the blocked CLONE_NEW* flags or the fail-closed path\n  (EPERM when clone_args cannot be read). A refactor could silently\n  reopen a namespace escape. Add guest tests that assert EPERM for\n  CLONE_NEWUSER, CLONE_NEWNS, CLONE_NEWPID and for an unreadable\n  clone_args struct.\n\n- [ ] **Document supervisor single-threaded invariant**\n  Notifications are processed by one supervisor loop thread, so the FD\n  table and path buffers are not concurrently mutated today. However,\n  this single-threaded invariant is implicit and undocumented. Add an\n  explicit comment/assert at the dispatch entry point. Audit the\n  narrower set of truly shared state (`shadow_sockets` mutex, any\n  signal-handler-accessible globals) for races if the loop is ever\n  parallelized.\n\n- [ ] **JIT spray mitigation for syscall rewrite fast-path**\n  The rewrite fast-path rewrites `syscall`/`sysenter`/`SVC` instructions\n  into trampoline calls at load time. JIT engines (V8, LuaJIT, Python)\n  emit executable code at runtime that the load-time rewriter never\n  sees. Threat classes:\n\n  (1) Hidden syscall instructions at misaligned offsets (x86-64 only).\n  (2) Trampoline entry from unregistered sites.\n  (3) W+X pages (the fundamental threat).\n  (4) MAP_SHARED aliasing bypass.\n\n  Phase 8 shipped per-VMA W^X enforcement and seccomp USER_NOTIF\n  backstop. Remaining hardening (all required for untrusted guests):\n  - W^X enforcement per backing object (not just per VMA -- MAP_SHARED\n    alias attack is not yet blocked)\n  - Scan-on-X at mprotect/mmap time (promotes JIT pages from Tier 1 to\n    Tier 2)\n  - Bitmap integrity (hook's dlmopen namespace or read-only after update)\n\n  Testing: guest test binaries for misaligned syscall, MAP_SHARED alias\n  attack, caller-origin bitmap rejection. Measure JIT-heavy workload\n  overhead.\n\n- [ ] **Supervisor-side Landlock enforcement** ([#14](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/14))\n  Apply a Landlock ruleset in the supervisor during initialization\n  (before spawning the guest) to confine its own host-level access:\n  read-only for system dirs and loader paths (runtime-detected),\n  read-write for the workspace/rootfs ext4 image, temp dirs, and\n  sockets. Requires `PR_SET_NO_NEW_PRIVS` before\n  `landlock_restrict_self()` and graceful fallback when Landlock is\n  unavailable. Network rules (TCP bind/connect deny) require Landlock\n  ABI v4+, gated on runtime kernel probing.\n\n## P1.5: Correctness (from Codex review, 2026-03-31)\n\n- [ ] **sendfile ignores short writes** (seccomp-dispatch.c:1906-1928)\n  `forward_sendfile` advances `total += n` by bytes read, not bytes\n  written. Both the LKL path (`kbox_lkl_write`) and host path\n  (`write()`) discard short-write residual. Silent data loss on pipes,\n  sockets, and nonblocking FDs. Fix: loop until all `n` bytes are\n  written or error; advance total by actual bytes written.\n\n- [ ] **ELF parser truncates oversized PT_INTERP instead of failing**\n  `kbox_find_elf_interp_loc` (elf.c:180) clamps overflow to `buf_len`\n  and silently truncates the interpreter path to `out_size - 1`. Callers\n  in dispatch-exec.c:459 trust the truncated path. A malformed ELF\n  selects the wrong interpreter instead of failing closed. Fix: reject\n  when `p_offset + p_filesz > buf_len`, require NUL terminator within\n  `p_filesz`, return error if path does not fit in `out`.\n\n- [ ] **Integer overflow in I/O emulation guest pointer arithmetic**\n  Several I/O paths add attacker-controlled guest addresses/offsets\n  without overflow checks: shadow pread at seccomp-dispatch.c:937,\n  guest writeback at :949, normal read/pread at :1694/:1710, write at\n  :1774, sendfile at :1890. A near-`UINT64_MAX` buffer pointer can\n  wrap to low memory. Guard with `__builtin_add_overflow`; reject\n  wrapped pointers with EFAULT and wrapped offsets with EOVERFLOW.\n\n- [ ] **kbox_vm_read_string returns stale errno on zero-length read**\n  procmem.c:347 returns `errno ? -errno : -EIO` when `process_vm_readv`\n  returns 0, but `errno` is undefined after a zero return. Fix: treat\n  `n == 0` as deterministic `-EFAULT`.\n\n## P2: Compatibility\n\n- [ ] **glibc-static: readlink(\"/proc/self/exe\") routed to LKL instead of host** ([#9](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/9))\n  `forward_readlinkat()` sends escape paths to LKL. `path.c` already\n  classifies `/proc/*/{exe,cwd,root}` as host-escape paths, but\n  `forward_readlinkat()` does not act on this classification for\n  readlink. Fix must be surgical: CONTINUE only for the specific magic\n  symlinks that the host kernel owns (`/proc/self/exe`), not a blanket\n  CONTINUE for all proc escape paths, which would break sandbox\n  assumptions. Unblocks glibc-static binaries.\n\n- [x] **FD gap: FDs in [1024, 32768) untracked** ([#8](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/8))\n  DONE (0000ea9). Added mid_fds[KBOX_MID_FD_MAX] array covering the\n  entire [1024, 32768) range. fd_lookup, fd_table_entry, all scan loops\n  updated. Gap is fully eliminated.\n\n- [ ] **File bind mounts: support or reject explicitly** ([#39](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/39))\n  `mount.c` always `mkdir()`s the target before `MS_BIND`, which fails\n  for file targets. Either create a regular file when the source is a\n  file, or reject file bind mounts early with a clear error message.\n\n- [x] **statfs/fstatfs CONTINUE leaks host filesystem metadata**\n  DONE (0000ea9). fstatfs moved from CONTINUE table to handler table\n  with fd_should_deny_io gating. Path-based statfs remains CONTINUE\n  (no FD, no pointer re-read risk).\n\n## P3: Test Coverage\n\n- [ ] **Guest test binaries must not soft-skip in CI**\n  Missing `/opt/tests/*` binaries produce SKIP instead of FAIL (in\n  `run-tests.sh`), so syscall regressions in dup, errno, signal, path,\n  and network coverage silently vanish from CI results. Make presence of\n  guest binaries a hard prerequisite, or build them as part of the test\n  target.\n\n- [ ] **Add mount/umount path handling tests**\n  No unit or integration tests cover mount-path behavior: relative\n  targets, normalization, host-root confinement, or virtual-path\n  classification for mount points.\n\n- [ ] **Triage stress test failures** ([#10](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/10))\n  Classify each of the 5 stress tests as deterministic or\n  timing-sensitive. Promote deterministic ones (fd-exhaust, rapid-fork)\n  to blocking in CI by removing `continue-on-error: true` from the\n  workflow for those jobs.\n\n- [ ] **io_uring block verification tests**\n  `io_uring_setup`, `io_uring_enter`, `io_uring_register` are in the\n  BPF deny list. No guest test verifies that these return EPERM. Add a\n  guest binary that attempts `io_uring_setup` and asserts the expected\n  denial, so a BPF refactor cannot silently re-enable io_uring (which\n  bypasses seccomp entirely).\n\n## P4: Enhancements\n\n- [ ] **Cache shadow memfds across repeated opens** ([#37](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/37))\n  `kbox_shadow_create()` rebuilds a fresh memfd on every O_RDONLY open\n  by copying the full file through LKL. An inode+mtime keyed cache that\n  reuses existing memfds would eliminate the copy on repeated opens,\n  cutting open+close latency roughly in half for hot files.\n\n- [ ] **Reverse-map host FDs to avoid O(n) close-path scans** ([#38](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/38))\n  `forward_close()` calls `kbox_fd_table_find_by_host_fd()` which\n  linearly scans 5120 slots. Add a host_fd-to-vfd reverse lookup (flat\n  array indexed by host_fd) and maintain a per-LKL-FD refcount to\n  eliminate both the reverse scan and the `lkl_fd_has_other_ref` scan.\n  Estimated impact: ~5-25us saved per close on shadowed FDs.\n\n- [ ] **Shrink kbox_fd_entry from 32 to ~20 bytes**\n  `lkl_fd` and `host_fd` are `long` but FD numbers are always 32-bit.\n  Use `int`. Pack boolean flags (`shadow_writeback`, `mirror_tty`,\n  `cloexec`) into a single `uint8_t` bitfield. Reduces FD table from\n  160KB to ~100KB, improving cache utilization for all scans.\n\n- [ ] **Shadow FD improvements** ([#11](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/11))\n  Configurable size cap (env var / CLI flag, 256MB default). Document\n  snapshot semantics. Staleness detection via mtime/size for\n  observability.\n\n- [ ] **SLIRP follow-up: server sockets and pidfd_getfd** ([#12](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/12))\n  Phase 6 shipped outbound sendmsg routing and TCP integration tests.\n  Remaining: replace SCM_RIGHTS with pidfd_getfd (un-allow-list\n  sendmsg), implement listen/accept with per-connection socketpair +\n  ADDFD injection.\n\n- [ ] **Performance comparison vs QEMU vs KVM**\n  In-tree microbenchmark exists (`tests/guest/bench-test`). Run\n  identical workloads under kbox, QEMU user-mode, QEMU system-mode, and\n  KVM. Publish comparative latency and throughput numbers.\n\n## P5: Architectural Evolution\n\n### Syscall rewriting remaining work\n\n- [ ] **BTC for bare x86_64 2-byte `syscall` (0F 05) sites** (~300 lines)\n  Relocate basic blocks to a Binary Translation Cache, patch original\n  with `jmp rel32`. Eliminates SIGSYS fallback for bare syscall sites.\n\n- [ ] **Synthetic vDSO for clock_gettime/gettimeofday**\n  Intercept at trampoline level, call host vDSO directly (bypasses\n  dispatch pipeline entirely). Also covers optimization target #4 in\n  the performance baseline section.\n\n- [ ] **cancel-wrapper (`__syscall_cancel`) fast-path correctness**\n  The two detected cancel-style Arm64 `open` wrappers break later\n  FD/runtime bookkeeping semantics when activated. Must preserve both\n  `__syscall_cancel` errno semantics and the same FD bookkeeping\n  behavior as the existing forwarder path before enabling.\n\n- [ ] **Full scan-on-X for JIT pages at mprotect time**\n  Promote JIT pages from Tier 1 (RET_TRAP) to Tier 2 (rewrite) by\n  scanning and rewriting syscall instructions when mprotect adds\n  PROT_EXEC.\n\n- [ ] **Integrate trampoline feasibility into kbox_collect_probe_result**\n\n- [ ] **Multi-threaded guest auto-downgrade to seccomp**\n  Currently CLONE_THREAD returns ENOSYS in trap/rewrite mode. Detect\n  and gracefully fall back to seccomp mode instead.\n\n### New architectures\n\n- [ ] **RISC-V (rv64) support** ([#18](https://github.com/sysprog21/kbox/issues/18))\n  Build with `make ARCH=riscv64`, run on `qemu-system-riscv64` with\n  standard Alpine rootfs. Requires LKL riscv64 support, open-flag ABI\n  tran