            "content": "# kbox - Project Instructions\n\n## What is kbox\nRootless chroot via seccomp-unotify + LKL (Linux Kernel Library). Intercepts\nguest syscalls and routes them to an in-process Linux kernel. Linux-only, runs\non x86_64 and aarch64.\n\n## Build\nLinux-only. Never attempt to build on macOS.\n\n```bash\n# Configure (interactive menuconfig, fetches Kconfiglib on first run)\nmake config\n\n# Or apply default config (all features enabled)\nmake defconfig\n\n# x86_64 (on node1)\nssh node1\ncd ~/TEMP/kbox && make defconfig && make\n\n# aarch64 development (lima VM, localhost)\nlima bash -c \"cd ~/playground/kbox && make defconfig && make\"\n\n# aarch64 benchmarking (real Arm64 host)\nssh arm\ncd ~/playground/kbox && make defconfig && make BUILD=release\n\n# debug build (ASAN/UBSAN) -- default\nmake defconfig && make\n```\n\nDeploy sources before building:\n- node1: `scp src/*.c node1:~/TEMP/kbox/src/` and headers similarly\n- lima: `lima bash -c \"cp -r /Users/jserv/playground/kbox/{src,include,tests,scripts,Makefile} ~/playground/kbox/\"`\n- arm: `scp -r src/*.c arm:~/playground/kbox/src/` and `scp -r include/kbox/*.h arm:~/playground/kbox/include/kbox/`\n\n## Test\n```bash\nmake check-unit                              # 249 unit tests, no LKL needed\n./scripts/run-tests.sh ./kbox alpine.ext4    # 47 integration tests\nmake check-stress                            # stress tests (non-blocking)\n```\n\nTest image `alpine.ext4` lives in ~/TEMP/kbox/ on node1 and ~/playground/kbox/ on lima and arm.\n\n## aarch64 Hosts\n- **lima**: aarch64 Linux VM on localhost. Use for development, unit tests,\n  integration tests, and iterating on features. Fast deploy (cp from macOS\n  shared filesystem).\n- **arm** (`ssh arm`): real Arm64 hardware. Use for benchmarking and\n  performance measurement. Deploy via scp. Performance numbers from lima\n  are not representative (VM overhead).\n\n## Code Style\n- C11 (`-std=gnu11`), `-Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic -Wshadow`\n- Follow `.clang-format` for formatting (requires `clang-format-20`)\n- macOS: `export PATH=/opt/homebrew/Cellar/llvm@20/20.1.8/bin:$PATH`\n- Filenames use hyphens, not underscores (e.g., `fd-table.c`, not `fd_table.c`)\n- Functions do one thing, max three indentation levels\n- No TODO comments, no stub implementations\n\n## Local-only Files\nThese files are local working documents. Never `git add` or commit them,\nand never list them in `.gitignore`:\n- `spec.md`\n- `CLAUDE.md`\n- `TODO.md`\n- `CHANGELOG.md`\n\n## Git Policy\nNever run `git commit`, `git reset`, `git rebase`, or `git push` unless\nexplicitly requested by the user.\n\nNever use `--no-verify` to bypass pre-commit hooks. If the hook fails,\nfix the underlying issue: reword comments that trigger false positives,\nadd cppcheck suppressions for pre-existing findings, or fix the hook\nitself. The hook exists to catch real problems; bypassing it defeats\nthe purpose.\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n### Source layout\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `src/` | All C source files |\n| `include/kbox/` | Public headers |\n| `tests/unit/` | Unit tests (no LKL dependency) |\n| `tests/guest/` | Guest test programs (static, run inside kbox) |\n| `tests/stress/` | Stress test programs (static, run inside kbox) |\n| `mk/` | Modular Makefile fragments |\n| `configs/` | Kconfig files and defconfig |\n| `scripts/` | Build helpers, test runners, git hooks |\n| `scripts/gdb/` | GDB helper commands |\n| `web/` | Frontend dashboard assets |\n| `docs/` | Documentation |\n\n### Key files\n- `src/seccomp-dispatch.c` -- main syscall dispatch (~4500 lines, largest file)\n- `src/seccomp-bpf.c` -- BPF filter generation\n- `src/fd-table.c` -- virtual FD table (three-range: low 0..1023, mid 1024..32767, high 32768+)\n- `src/shadow-fd.c` -- memfd shadows for O_RDONLY files (enables mmap)\n- `src/path.c` -- path normalization and virtual/host routing\n- `src/elf.c` -- ELF parser, PT_INTERP extraction\n- `src/mount.c` -- mount profiles (raw, recommended, standard)\n- `include/kbox/lkl-wrap.h` -- LKL stat struct and ABI translation\n\n### Critical ABI rules\n- LKL uses asm-generic stat (128 bytes). Host x86_64 stat is 144 bytes.\n  Always use `struct kbox_lkl_stat` + `kbox_lkl_stat_to_host()`.\n- seccomp args[] zero-extend 32-bit values. Use `to_dirfd_arg()` for sign extension.\n- aarch64 O_* flags differ from asm-generic. Translate bidirectionally.\n\n### FD table design\n- `KBOX_FD_BASE=32768` splits virtual FDs into three ranges\n- `entries[]` for FDs >= 32768 (normal LKL allocation)\n- `low_fds[1024]` for FDs 0..1023 (dup2/dup3, stdio, pipes)\n- `mid_fds[31744]` for FDs 1024..32767 (host-passthrough tracking)\n- `KBOX_LKL_FD_SHADOW_ONLY` sentinel marks host-passthrough FDs\n- I/O handlers return EBADF for untracked FDs (lkl_fd == -1)\n- No CONTINUE for pointer-dependent paths (emulated in supervisor)\n\n### BPF filter\n- `close` is NOT in the allow list (goes through USER_NOTIF -> forward_close)\n- `sendmsg` IS in the allow list (child pre-exec SCM_RIGHTS)\n\n## Review Workflow\nImplement -> self-review -> Gemini + Codex MCP (parallel) -> consensus fixes -> rebuild + retest.\n",
